msgid "Catching a horse..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0001"
msgid "Good horses?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0002"
msgid "How do I train one?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0003"
msgid "No, I'm fine."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near_01"
msgid "Phwee..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near_02"
msgid "Nay..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>Hey, Shibo... You think this nosy guy right here\n"
"is interested in horses?<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>Looks like it to me, Darton... Judging from his eyes,\n"
"he's just itching to get into the saddle.<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Wild horses get scared easily, and if they\n"
"notice people near them, they'll take off.\n"
"\n"
"Just sneak up on 'em from behind real\n"
"slow. When you get good and close...\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>grab 'em and jump on quick!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Horses with <2.se_co>spots <3.re_co>on them are even-\n"
"tempered and easy to train.\n"
"\n"
"On the other hand, horses that are all\n"
"<4.se_co>one color<5.re_co>, like straight black or white,\n"
"are a bit more wild and harder to train."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>They're really wild, so they'll run in\n"
"different directions and buck here and\n"
"there because they aren't trained yet.\n"
"When that happens, you've gotta soothe\n"
"them!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid "<1.so>Hey, mister! Ya get all that?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Dad taught us a lot.\n"
"Just leave the horsin' around to us!<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>You're right. He's got eyes that just say, like...\n"
"\"Nothing in this world matters to me\n"
"except horses.\"<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: pause (long)
#. 5: text_size
#. 6: choice
msgctxt "talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Do you want to hear some tips to help\n"
"you master your horse?<2.pa> Yay or neigh?\n"
"\n"
"<3.te_si>I didn't think of that joke, by the way.<4.pa> That's one\n"
"of my dad's jokes!<5.te_si><6.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: sound
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.so>That means...<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk14"
msgid "<1.so><2.te_si>THAT MEANS...<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That means we've got ourselves\n"
"a customer!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (long)
#. 6: set_colour (blue)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Howdy, mister man!<2.pa> Welcome to\n"
"<3.se_co>Dueling Peaks Stables<4.re_co>!\n"
"\n"
"Or...<5.pa>welcome to the front of\n"
"<6.se_co>Dueling Peaks Stables<7.re_co>, I guess."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You really can tell just by looking into\n"
"his eyes!\n"
"\n"
"Bro, his head is just filled with horse\n"
"stuff, right?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That's right! Just look at his eyes!<2.pa>\n"
"Right now in his head, it's all<3.pa> horses,\n"
"horses, horses, food, and horses...right?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>In that case, you should feel free to ask\n"
"us anything at all about horses!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you crouch and sneak up quietly...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>they won't notice you!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk21"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But a <2.se_co>one-color<3.re_co> horse has more\n"
"stamina and runs faster, right?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk22"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Dad said they're hard to handle at first,\n"
"but if you spend a lot of time with a\n"
"<2.se_co>one-color <3.re_co>horse, you'll be best buds!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
#. 5: set_colour (blue)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk23"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Dad also said that beginners should start\n"
"with <2.se_co>spotted <3.re_co>horses...<4.pa> When I grow up,\n"
"I'll ride a <5.se_co>one-color<6.re_co> horse, though!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk24"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But dad also said that just constantly\n"
"soothing them won't do at all."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk25"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The trick is to soothe them when they do\n"
"what you want them to do.\n"
"\n"
"It's like saying \"thanks\" to them for a job\n"
"well done!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk26"
msgid ""
"<1.so>See ya! Bye-bye!<2.pa>\n"
"Take care, now!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk27"
msgid "<1.so>Look, Shibo, it's the twinless dude!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk28"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Look, Darton, it's theâ€”<2.pa>\n"
"Oh,<3.pa> you already said that."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk29"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Dad taught us a lot! If you wanna know\n"
"about horses, just ask us!<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk30"
msgid "<1.so><2.te_si>So sleepy...<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (longer)
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk31"
msgid ""
"<1.te_si><2.so>One spotted horse...<3.pa>\n"
"Two spotted horses...<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk33"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Today I'm gonna beat <2.se_co>Darton<3.re_co>\n"
"to the place where the horses are!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk34"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My dad was the second-best horse\n"
"guy, you know!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk35"
msgid "<1.so>All right! I got here before Darton!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk36"
msgid "<1.so>Pretty impressive, right!"
msgstr ""

